__________________________________________________<br>
<br>
From http://www.galeforcenine.com/gamers/wfb/<br>
<br>
Thursday, November 14, 2002 <br>
GW GT 2003 Season - Rumors confirmed - Get all your info here and <br>
now!!! <br>
Information from an interview with Joe Krone about the 2003 GT season <br>
by Jason Holliday. <br>
<br>
Thanks for stopping by to check out all the new information for the <br>
new 2003 GT season. <br>
<br>
I spoke to Joe Krone and he filled me in on a lot of the new stuff to <br>
see and expect during the coming year. So enjoy, and come back often <br>
for more updates and great articles in the GF9 Warhammer Forum. <br>
<br>
There are now 9 GT's, they will be in the following cities and will be <br>
on the following dates, and yes these are confirmed. <br>
<br>
- Minneapolis, MN - Feb 7-9 <br>
- Baltimore, MD - March 7-9 <br>
- Seattle, WA - April 4-6 <br>
- Chicago, IL - May 9-11 <br>
- Philly, Penn - June 13-15 <br>
- Charlotte, NC - Aug 22-24 <br>
- Dallas, TX - Sept 26-28 <br>
- Los Angeles, CA - Oct 17-19 <br>
- Columbus, OH - Oct 31-Nov 2 <br>
<br>
There are new point limits for Fantasy and 40K. <br>
<br>
- Fantasy is now 2150 from 2000 <br>
- 40K is now 1850 from 1700 <br>
<br>
Since the points have been increased, the game time has been <br>
increased. The new time limit is 2.5 hours from 2.25 hours. The wait <br>
time will also be decreased, but that will take time and GW has to <br>
work out the bugs, so hopefully by the 2nd GT you will see shorter <br>
wait times, maybe as short as 15-20 minutes between games. <br>
<br>
The new start time will be on Saturday at 8:30 am, and will end about <br>
the same time. <br>
<br>
Player Judging, everyones favorite! Players will now judge or vote on <br>
the following. <br>
<br>
- Players choice. The new system will give players points for each <br>
vote they receive for players choice, and these points will be <br>
allocated to the players overall appearance score. So if John Doe gets <br>
20 votes, and Bob Smith gets none, well that is just to bad, John will <br>
get X number of points added to his score and Bob will get jack <br>
nothing added. So if you want extra points make em look good!! <br>
<br>
Comp, the Comp system as we know it has been removed. The new system <br>
is not as dramatic and is less prevalent. The new category will be <br>
called "Theme", and the basic rule is this. Would your army be an army <br>
in the Warhammer or 40K universe. This however is not saying you can't <br>
bring that 40K Hockey army. The presence of "Theme" allows a creative <br>
way of painting and collecting your army. The judging system is not <br>
finalized so stay tuned for this one. Also, player judged Comp is out <br>
the window, so that guy you just wasted with your all Marauder army on <br>
foot can't score you low on Comp just cause his lost. <br>
<br>
Extended Rules. There will be Extended Rules for all the GT's this <br>
year, and the great thing about this is, all the Extended Rules will <br>
be different for each GT. One GT may ask you to bring messengers and <br>
markers, the next one may ask you to bring 300 points of special <br>
troops, the next maybe be 100 points core and 250 points of rare <br>
troops. Basically be prepared for anything!!! <br>
<br>
Games Workshop is also working on a new website for the GTs , so be on <br>
the look out for the new site. It should hopefully be up and running <br>
around Thanksgiving time. I am sure it will be an internal thing from <br>
the main site, but the GT page will give you all the information you <br>
will need for the GT season, and will give you all the information you <br>
will need for the GT 9 months away so you are not stuck with having to <br>
paint 300 points of special troops in 30 days cause you just found <br>
out. <br>
<br>
The awards will also change due to the fact that "Selection" is no <br>
longer a category. Look for some new categories. <br>
<br>
Well, that is all for now, take away from this what you will, and we <br>
